    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWe are maintaining Cython on Fedora and currently updating from 3.0.12 to 3.1.2\n\ntest_python_builtin_compatibiliy added [here](https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/da405c6c58fd0b35f723c8efea4b76997cf76716) fails on our CI with:\n\n======================================================================\nFAIL: test_python_builtin_compatibility (Cython.Compiler.Tests.TestBuiltin.TestBuiltinCompatibility.test_python_builtin_compatibility)\n\\----------------------------------------------------------------------\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/var/ARTIFACTS/work-planu5k1d98q/plan/discover/default-0/source/cython-3.1.2/Cython/Compiler/Tests/TestBuiltin.py\", line 52, in test_python_builtin_compatibility\n    self.assertSetEqual(runtime_builtins, expected_builtins)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nAssertionError: Items in the first set but not the second:\n\\'__IPYTHON\\__'\n'ip'\n'display'\n'_ip'\n'get_ipython'\n\nWe install ipython from PyPI to test and it looks like it's adding \\_\\_IPYTHON__ and get_ipython to the runtime_builtins\n\n\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n# example code\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n_No response_\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.1.2\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
